CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper March 12, 1955, pg. 16, reads: "At Foster Babies Conference - When the conference on child care was held at Central Baptist Church Tuesday evening, a great deal of the discussion centered around the need for foster parents for children whose are is paid for by the Juvenile Court and the need for adoption of Negro babies.  Left to right, among those who took part, were Alexander J. Allen, Mrs. Alice Brady, Mrs. George L. West, Mrs. Helen Dandridge and the Rev. C. S. Butcher. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Alexander J. Allen, Alice Brady, Mrs. George L. West, Helen Dandridge and Rev. C. S. Butcher at conference on child care at Central Baptist Church, with Urban League of Pittsburgh banner in background
